objectDesc.p: Papyrus, 17.3x8.5 (?), 1 extant leaf(s), 1 column(s), 28 (?) line(s) per column, 24? characters per line, written in Greek.

history.provenance: Excavated 1896-1897 by Bernard Grenfell and Arthur Hunt, Egypt Exploration Society at Al Bahnasā, Miṣr from a garbage dump.
Donated pre 1904 to Cambridge University Library at Cambridge, England.

msIdentifier.msName: Add. Ms. 4048, Cambridge University Library, Cambridge, England.

sourceDesc.bibl: Grenfell, Bernard P. and Arthur S. Hunt, The Oxyrhynchus Papyri, vol. 2, no. 210, Egypt Exploration Society: London, England, 1899. OCLC 855777953.
